llapse) is required over the redshift range\n$3<z<10$ for a single galaxy cluster with mass $\\sim3\\times10^{14}$ $M_\\odot$\nat z=0. These SNe might be visible in observations of high-redshift clusters\nand protoclusters with the James Webb Space Telescope.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 May 2021 19:49:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 25 Oct 2021 19:31:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 16 Feb 2022 22:31:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-18"}
