 In the second regime,\nwhen several chemical potentials reach rather large values, one could observe a\nrather complicated and rich phase structure, and $\\mu_5$ can be a factor that\nnot so much catalyzes as {\\it triggers} rather peculiar phases. For example, it\ncan lead to the formation of diquark condensation at zero baryon chemical\npotential.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 May 2021 11:45:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 19 May 2021 16:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-31"}
